#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:-1
msgid ""
"Learn how Spack's bootstrapping feature automatically fetches and installs "
"essential build tools when they are not available on the host system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:16
msgid "Bootstrapping"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:18
msgid ""
"In the :ref:`Getting started <getting_started>` section, we already "
"mentioned that Spack can bootstrap some of its dependencies, including "
"``clingo``. In fact, there is an entire command dedicated to the management "
"of every aspect of bootstrapping:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:23
msgid ""
"Spack bootstraps its dependencies automatically the first time they are "
"needed. You can readily check if any prerequisite for using Spack is missing "
"by running:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:26
msgid ""
"% spack bootstrap status\n"
"Spack v0.19.0 - python@3.8\n"
"\n"
"[FAIL] Core Functionalities\n"
"  [B] MISSING \"clingo\": required to concretize specs\n"
"\n"
"[FAIL] Binary packages\n"
"  [B] MISSING \"gpg2\": required to sign/verify buildcaches\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"Spack will take care of bootstrapping any missing dependency marked as [B]. "
"Dependencies marked as [-] are instead required to be found on the system.\n"
"\n"
"% echo $?\n"
"1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:43
msgid ""
"In the case of the output shown above, Spack detected that both ``clingo`` "
"and ``gnupg`` are missing, and it's giving detailed information on why they "
"are needed and whether they can be bootstrapped. The return code of this "
"command summarizes the results; if any dependencies are missing, the return "
"code is ``1``, otherwise ``0``. Running a command that concretizes a spec, "
"like:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:47
msgid ""
"% spack solve zlib\n"
"==> Installing \"clingo-bootstrap@spack%apple-clang@12.0.0~docs~ipo+python "
"build_type=Release arch=darwin-catalina-x86_64\" from a buildcache\n"
"[ ... ]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:53
msgid ""
"automatically triggers the bootstrapping of clingo from pre-built binaries "
"as expected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:55
msgid ""
"Users can also bootstrap all Spack's dependencies in a single command, which "
"is useful to set up containers or other similar environments:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:57
msgid ""
"$ spack bootstrap now\n"
"==> Installing \"clingo-"
"bootstrap@spack%gcc@10.2.1~docs~ipo+python+static_libstdcpp "
"build_type=Release arch=linux-centos7-x86_64\" from a buildcache\n"
"==> Installing \"patchelf@0.15.0%gcc@10.2.1 ldflags=\"-static-libstdc++ -"
"static-libgcc\"  arch=linux-centos7-x86_64\" from a buildcache"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:66
msgid "The Bootstrapping Store"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:68
msgid ""
"The software installed for bootstrapping purposes is deployed in a separate "
"store. You can check its location with the following command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:71
msgid "% spack bootstrap root"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:75
msgid "You can also change it by specifying the desired path:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:77
msgid "% spack bootstrap root /opt/spack/bootstrap"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:81
msgid ""
"You can check what is installed in the bootstrapping store at any time using:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:83
msgid ""
"% spack -b find\n"
"==> Showing internal bootstrap store at \"/Users/spack/.spack/bootstrap/"
"store\"\n"
"==> 11 installed packages\n"
"-- darwin-catalina-x86_64 / apple-clang@12.0.0 ------------------\n"
"clingo-bootstrap@spack  libassuan@2.5.5  libgpg-error@1.42  libksba@1.5.1  "
"pinentry@1.1.1  zlib@1.2.11\n"
"gnupg@2.3.1             libgcrypt@1.9.3  libiconv@1.16      npth@1.6       "
"python@3.8"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:92
msgid ""
"If needed, you can remove all the software in the current bootstrapping "
"store with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:94
msgid ""
"% spack clean -b\n"
"==> Removing bootstrapped software and configuration in \"/Users/spack/."
"spack/bootstrap\"\n"
"\n"
"% spack -b find\n"
"==> Showing internal bootstrap store at \"/Users/spack/.spack/bootstrap/"
"store\"\n"
"==> 0 installed packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:109
msgid "Enabling and Disabling Bootstrapping Methods"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:111
msgid "Bootstrapping is performed by trying the methods listed by:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:115
msgid ""
"in the order they appear, from top to bottom. By default, Spack is "
"configured to try bootstrapping from pre-built binaries first and to fall "
"back to bootstrapping from sources if that fails."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:118
msgid "If needed, you can disable bootstrapping altogether by running:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:120
msgid "% spack bootstrap disable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:124
msgid ""
"in which case, it's your responsibility to ensure Spack runs in an "
"environment where all its prerequisites are installed. You can also "
"configure Spack to skip certain bootstrapping methods by disabling them "
"specifically:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:127
msgid ""
"% spack bootstrap disable github-actions\n"
"==> \"github-actions\" is now disabled and will not be used for bootstrapping"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:132
msgid ""
"tells Spack to skip trying to bootstrap from binaries. To add the \"github-"
"actions\" method back, you can:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:135
msgid "% spack bootstrap enable github-actions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:139
msgid "You can also reset the bootstrapping configuration to Spack's defaults:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:141
msgid ""
"% spack bootstrap reset\n"
"==> Bootstrapping configuration is being reset to Spack's defaults. Current "
"configuration will be lost.\n"
"Do you want to continue? [Y/n]\n"
"%"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:152
msgid "Creating a Mirror for Air-Gapped Systems"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:154
msgid ""
"Spack's default bootstrapping configuration requires internet connection to "
"fetch precompiled binaries or source tarballs. Sometimes, though, Spack is "
"deployed on air-gapped systems where such access is denied."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:157
msgid ""
"To help in these situations, Spack provides a command to create a local "
"mirror containing the source tarballs and/or binary packages needed for "
"bootstrapping."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:159
msgid ""
"% spack bootstrap mirror --binary-packages /opt/bootstrap\n"
"==> Adding \"clingo-bootstrap@spack+python %apple-clang target=x86_64\" and "
"dependencies to the mirror at /opt/bootstrap/local-mirror\n"
"==> Adding \"gnupg@2.3: %apple-clang target=x86_64\" and dependencies to the "
"mirror at /opt/bootstrap/local-mirror\n"
"==> Adding \"patchelf@0.13.1:0.13.99 %apple-clang target=x86_64\" and "
"dependencies to the mirror at /opt/bootstrap/local-mirror\n"
"==> Adding binary packages from \"https://github.com/alalazo/spack-bootstrap-"
"mirrors/releases/download/v0.1-rc.2/bootstrap-buildcache.tar.gz\" to the "
"mirror at /opt/bootstrap/local-mirror\n"
"\n"
"To register the mirror on the platform where it's supposed to be used run "
"the following command(s):\n"
"  % spack bootstrap add --trust local-sources /opt/bootstrap/metadata/"
"sources\n"
"  % spack bootstrap add --trust local-binaries /opt/bootstrap/metadata/"
"binaries\n"
"  % spack buildcache update-index /opt/bootstrap/bootstrap_cache"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../bootstrapping.rst:172
msgid ""
"Run this command on a machine with internet access, then move the resulting "
"folder to the air-gapped system. Once the local sources are added using the "
"commands suggested at the prompt, they can be used to bootstrap Spack."
msgstr ""
